                    <div class="quiz-question">
                        <p><strong>Question 2:</strong> What should you do before implementing an AI tool in your classroom?</p>
                        <ul class="quiz-options">
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Try it immediately with students</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, true)">Check district policies and get approval</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Wait for other teachers to try it first</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Only use it for administrative tasks</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="quiz-question">
                        <p><strong>Question 3:</strong> Which approach best describes ethical AI use in education?</p>
                        <ul class="quiz-options">
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Replace teacher decision-making with AI</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, true)">Use AI to enhance teaching while maintaining human oversight</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Allow students unlimited access to any AI tool</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">Avoid AI completely in educational settings</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="quiz-question">
                        <p><strong>Question 4:</strong> What is a key characteristic of effective AI prompts?</p>
                        <ul class="quiz-options">
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">They should be as short as possible</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, true)">They should be specific and provide clear context</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">They should use technical jargon</li>
                            <li onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, false)">They should be identical for all use cases</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div id="quiz-results" style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 20px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 10px; display: none;">
                        <h4 id="results-title"></h4>
                        <p id="results-message"></p>
                        <div class="progress-bar">
                            <div class="progress-fill" id="quiz-progress"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <button class="btn" onclick="submitQuiz()" id="submit-quiz" style="display: none;">Submit Quiz</button>
                </div>

                <div class="interactive-element">
                    <h4>💭 Reflection Questions</h4>
                    <p>Consider these questions and jot down your thoughts:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>How might AI tools enhance your specific teaching or support role?</li>
                        <li>What concerns do you have about implementing AI in your work?</li>
                        <li>What steps will you take to stay informed about AI developments?</li>
                    </ul>
                    <textarea placeholder="Share your reflections here..." style="width: 100%; height: 120px; margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 5px;"></textarea>
                    <button class="btn" onclick="saveReflections()">Save Reflections</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Resources Section -->
        <section class="content-section" id="resources">
